      • waitAvailable

        public void waitAvailable(boolean wait_for_frame_to_be_available)
        When "true", the thread waits until a new frame is available for transfer. The default value is "true".
        Parameters:
        wait_for_frame_to_be_available -

      • getFrame

        public byte[] getFrame(byte[] buffer)
        Copies the available frame-buffer data into the given buffer. If buffer is null or of the wrong size, it gets (re)allocated. In any case a buffer containing the current frame gets returned.

      • getFrame

        public void getFrame(int[] pixels)
        Fills the given pixels-array with the current frame-buffer. "pixels" needs to be allocated and resized to the full framesize. The Pixels are formated either as 0xAARRGGBB or 0xAABBGGRR, depending on chosen format (Format.RGB or Format.BGR)
